HEADWORD: acetonuria
<hw>ac`e*to*nu"ri*a</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧s`⟦esl⟧*t⟦osl⟧*n⟦umac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>acetone</er>; <er>Urine</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Excess of ketone bodies (including acetone, acetoacetic acid and
beta-hydroxybutyric acid) in the urine, as in starvation or
diabetes</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b>ketonuria</syn>⟦br⟧
